1
00:01:37,458 --> 00:01:40,916
♪

2
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,875
[MAYUKA]
I’m bored!

3
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:48,375
[yawn]

4
00:01:48,458 --> 00:01:50,625
It’s been nothing but
desert outside for hours.

5
00:01:50,708 --> 00:01:53,125
Are we really heading
the right way?

6
00:01:53,208 --> 00:01:55,625
Garbond’s run-down, and out
in the middle of nowhere.

7
00:01:55,708 --> 00:01:58,875
Perfect hiding place for
men with guilty consciences.

8
00:01:58,958 --> 00:02:00,208
[MAN ON RADIO]
Status report?

9
00:02:00,291 --> 00:02:01,875
Another voice?

10
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:03,375
Hey, I’ve been meaning to ask
about those transmissions.

11
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:04,666
What are they?

12
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:06,000
[VIDAUX]
I’m tapping into communications

13
00:02:06,083 --> 00:02:07,750
from local police scanners.

14
00:02:07,833 --> 00:02:09,416
We’re all on the lam, after all.

15
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,083
[DERRIDA]
Right.

16
00:02:11,166 --> 00:02:13,208
[VIDAUX] Don’t worry.
Haven’t heard anything bad yet.

17
00:02:13,291 --> 00:02:14,625
-[MAYUKA] Hey, look!
-[BOTH] Huh?

18
00:02:14,708 --> 00:02:16,916
[MAYUKA] It says 50 kilometers
to the next city!

19
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,625
[VIDAUX] Guess we’ll make
it before sundown, at least.

20
00:02:19,708 --> 00:02:21,041
[engine roar]

21
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,291
Do you think we’ll
find Mage there?

22
00:02:24,375 --> 00:02:25,625
[DERRIDA]
That security camera footage

23
00:02:25,708 --> 00:02:27,416
was from quite a while back.

24
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,541
She might not be in
the city anymore.

25
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:31,541
[YURI]
But maybe,

26
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:33,333
we’ll find some kind of clue,

27
00:02:33,416 --> 00:02:34,583
-or...
-[explosions]

28
00:02:34,666 --> 00:02:36,916
-What the?!
-What was that?!

29
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,125
That’s not good!

30
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:39,666
-[DERRIDA] Ah!
-[rocks tumbling]

31
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,166
-[grunt]
-[engine roar]

32
00:02:42,125 --> 00:02:43,916
[rocks crashing]

33
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:46,375
[explosion]

34
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,000
That seemed like a trap.

35
00:02:48,083 --> 00:02:49,708
Those government guys again?

36
00:02:49,791 --> 00:02:51,708
-[DERRIDA] Or Donna?
-[VIDAUX] Buckle up!

37
00:02:53,208 --> 00:02:54,791
[DISTORTED VOICE]
Exit the highway now.

38
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:56,625
If you rush forward
trying to avoid this,

39
00:02:56,708 --> 00:02:58,041
you’ll get caught
in the real trap.

40
00:02:58,125 --> 00:02:59,416
Who are you?

41
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:00,541
-[VOICE] You’ve been advised.
-[BOTH gasp]

42
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:02,250
[DERRIDA]
What just happened?

43
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:04,083
[GRAHAM] Our radio tap
system was intercepted

44
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:05,416
by an outside source.

45
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,291
Unable to pinpoint
the signal’s origin.

46
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:08,666
We can’t change routes!

47
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:10,208
If we leave the highway,
it’ll take longer.

48
00:03:10,291 --> 00:03:11,500
But what if it
really is dangerous

49
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:12,625
to keep on going this way?

50
00:03:12,708 --> 00:03:14,083
-[VIDAUX sighs]
-[engine roar]

51
00:03:14,166 --> 00:03:15,000
[grunt]

52
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:15,958
[tires screech]

53
00:03:17,166 --> 00:03:18,125
[DONNA]
What?

54
00:03:18,208 --> 00:03:20,375
Was I detected?

55
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:22,000
No.

56
00:03:24,083 --> 00:03:25,583
[ANDREI on phone]
Donna?

57
00:03:25,666 --> 00:03:28,416
Is it true you haven’t
finished Derrida off yet?

58
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:31,916
Say something, I want answers!

59
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,625
You’re a clever little rat.

60
00:03:33,708 --> 00:03:35,750
I see that you decided
to listen in on me.

61
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:36,833
[gasp]

62
00:03:36,916 --> 00:03:38,250
I wasn’t eavesdropping at all!

63
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:39,958
[DONNA]
A pitiful rat,

64
00:03:40,041 --> 00:03:42,625
who foolishly trampled
upon Death’s shadow.

65
00:03:42,708 --> 00:03:44,500
[ANDREI]
Wait, Death?

66
00:03:44,583 --> 00:03:46,333
I...
I haven’t trampled on anything!

67
00:03:46,416 --> 00:03:47,916
[DONNA]
That was a mistake.

68
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,416
You won’t live to see
the light of another day.

69
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:53,625
Your time in this world will
be cut short by Death’s scythe.

70
00:03:53,708 --> 00:03:54,666
[gasp]

71
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,208
Wait, Donna please, spare me,

72
00:03:56,291 --> 00:03:57,250
-I’m begging--!
-[hangs up]

73
00:03:58,583 --> 00:04:00,125
[engine roars]

74
00:04:00,208 --> 00:04:02,250
[wind blowing]

75
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,583
[MAYUKA] Ah!
There are real beds here, right?

76
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:09,791
-[YURI] And showers, too?!
[DERRIDA] Is this wise?

77
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:13,000
Staying at a hotel seems
like asking to be attacked.

78
00:04:13,083 --> 00:04:14,666
[VIDAUX]
Not if it’s Donna.

79
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,958
She’ll only strike in places
without many people around.

80
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:19,708
She doesn’t seem the type to
worry about casualties, though.

81
00:04:19,791 --> 00:04:21,541
[VIDAUX]
She prefers not to reveal her MO

82
00:04:21,625 --> 00:04:22,791
to anyone but her targets.

83
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:24,750
The heavy weapons’ll
slow you down,

84
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:26,750
but when she kills,
she makes it personal.

85
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,083
So even if she mixes
in with a crowd,

86
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:30,791
she won’t try to blow
us up with a bomb

87
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:33,041
or anything
we can’t see coming.

88
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:36,583
A veteran assassin like Donna
would never alter her style.

89
00:04:41,041 --> 00:04:42,875
I’ll meet up with you all later.

90
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:44,458
You’re not coming upstairs,
Papa?

91
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:46,250
I’m gonna go look around.

92
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:47,416
You stay here.

93
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,041
-I want to come with you.
-No.

94
00:04:49,125 --> 00:04:51,583
I need you to stick with
Mayuka and Yuri for me.

95
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:53,333
Just in case, okay?

96
00:04:53,416 --> 00:04:54,458
Mm-hmm.

97
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:00,875
♪

98
00:05:10,083 --> 00:05:11,416
[BARTENDER]
What’ll it be?

99
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,333
Just milk.

100
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:14,500
[laughter]

101
00:05:15,458 --> 00:05:16,666
[BARTENDER]
Sorry, pal,

102
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:17,958
but we’ve only
got the hard stuff here.

103
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:26,916
Not bad at all!

104
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,750
Let’s get a round for
the whole house, on me!

105
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:31,291
[cheering]

106
00:05:31,375 --> 00:05:33,333
Actually,
I’m looking for someone.

107
00:05:36,291 --> 00:05:38,583
[YURI] I’m getting
the hot water started!

108
00:05:38,666 --> 00:05:40,208
[MAYUKA, YURI giggle]

109
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:42,666
[DISTORTED VOICE]
Exit the highway now.

110
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,333
You’ve been advised.

111
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:47,000
[DERRIDA]
“Advised”, huh?

112
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:49,541
[yawn]

113
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:50,458
[groan]

114
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:52,458
[YURI giggles]

115
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:54,541
♪

116
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:58,666
[sigh]

117
00:06:04,791 --> 00:06:07,083
-[YURI] Aren’t you gonna sleep?
-Probably in a bit.

118
00:06:07,166 --> 00:06:08,625
Don’t wait up for me, okay?

119
00:06:08,708 --> 00:06:10,583
You look like something’s
on your mind. What’s up?

120
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:13,708
When do I ever not have
something on my mind?

121
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:18,458
That voice. The one we heard
on the comm this afternoon.

122
00:06:18,541 --> 00:06:20,750
I feel like I’ve heard
it somewhere before.

123
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:22,916
Really? Recently?

124
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,125
Think so.

125
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:25,625
It wasn’t that long ago.

126
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:26,958
Though, uh...

127
00:06:27,041 --> 00:06:28,875
I guess it was about
10 years ago for you.

128
00:06:28,958 --> 00:06:31,125
How did you recognize it
through the distortion?

129
00:06:31,208 --> 00:06:32,416
Didn’t have to.

130
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,416
It's the distorted voice
that’s familiar.

131
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,208
[VIDAUX]
Both of you are still up?

132
00:06:36,291 --> 00:06:38,416
You should be taking
this chance to rest.

133
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,583
You find out
anything out there?

134
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:42,291
[VIDAUX]
Nothing about Mage.

135
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:45,500
However, I did learn that
there’s a Destruct in town

136
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:47,333
who sounds like
he could be Cassiel.

137
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:49,166
What? You’re kidding me!
Where is he?

138
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:52,541
That info, I couldn’t get.

139
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,541
He’s a very cautious guy,
it seems.

140
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:56,000
[sigh]

141
00:06:57,875 --> 00:06:59,416
One more bit of bad news.

142
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:02,375
Rumor has it there’s someone
else looking for Cassiel.

143
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:04,208
A woman with a scar on her face.

144
00:07:04,291 --> 00:07:06,208
Sounds like Donna!
But why is she here?

145
00:07:06,291 --> 00:07:08,125
Maybe she traced him
based on the information

146
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:10,000
in the file we stole
from Rebuild.

147
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:11,375
Oh, great.

148
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:13,333
-We need to find him first!
-[radio static]

149
00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:14,916
[DISTORTED VOICE]
Don’t be hasty.

150
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,875
[gasp]

151
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,083
Impossible!

152
00:07:19,166 --> 00:07:20,875
My ID is void.

153
00:07:20,958 --> 00:07:23,583
-It can’t get calls!
-Destroy that thing, now!

154
00:07:23,666 --> 00:07:25,000
[DISTORTED VOICE]
Oh?

155
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:26,250
But you listened to my
advice on the highway,

156
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:28,458
and that turned
out in your favor.

157
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:29,416
Hang on a second.

158
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,750
I get it now.

159
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,500
It’s you, isn’t it, Cassiel?

160
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:33,416
I’m right, aren’t I?

161
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,458
Huh?

162
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:36,333
You saying that’s him? You sure?

163
00:07:36,416 --> 00:07:37,833
I remember.

164
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:40,458
Just before I could
finish up the patch file,

165
00:07:40,541 --> 00:07:42,125
I got a call that
warned me to review

166
00:07:42,208 --> 00:07:44,750
the quality control
process for the DZs.

167
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,916
He scrambled his voice
the same way.

168
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,083
Isn’t that correct, Cassiel?

169
00:07:49,166 --> 00:07:52,666
[CASSIEL] You remember one
phone call from 10 years ago?

170
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:54,875
It wasn’t actually
10 years ago for me.

171
00:07:54,958 --> 00:07:57,416
[CASSIEL]
Cryostasis, then.

172
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:59,458
It’s just as
Mage Bilstein said.

173
00:07:59,541 --> 00:08:00,916
You spoke with her?!

174
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,583
[CASSIEL] I knew you’d
come here eventually.

175
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:05,083
I want to talk to you.

176
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:06,875
Yeah, me too!
[gasp]

177
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:08,458
We’d all like to meet you.

178
00:08:08,541 --> 00:08:10,583
What’s your location?

179
00:08:10,666 --> 00:08:12,333
[CASSIEL]
No. You’re under observation

180
00:08:12,416 --> 00:08:14,541
of that assassin, Donna.

181
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:16,291
How do you know?

182
00:08:16,375 --> 00:08:18,375
And we just heard a rumor that
she’s going after you, too, now.

183
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:20,250
That’s what she’s up to.

184
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:22,291
She intentionally let
that information slip

185
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:24,375
to the bartender
to get all of us to panic.

186
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:26,875
[CASSIEL] Her plan is to
have you search for me,

187
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:29,041
and then finish us
all off together.

188
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:32,541
I don’t think she appreciated
me tapping her communications.

189
00:08:32,625 --> 00:08:34,833
What’re you planning to do?

190
00:08:34,916 --> 00:08:36,916
I’ll leak information
on my whereabouts

191
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,125
to draw the attention
away from you.

192
00:08:39,208 --> 00:08:42,541
At dawn, leave the hotel
and drive west on the highway.

193
00:08:42,625 --> 00:08:44,291
I’ll find you from there.

194
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:46,958
Careful not to
underestimate Donna.

195
00:08:47,041 --> 00:08:48,458
[CASSIEL]
I won’t.

196
00:08:48,541 --> 00:08:51,208
Plus, I have a bit of
an ace-in-the-hole myself.

197
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:53,083
-See you at dawn.
-[hangs up]

198
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:55,541
[YURI sighs]

199
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:59,458
♪

200
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:04,375
[sigh]

201
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,250
[VIDAUX]
It’s almost time.

202
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,833
Let them sleep as
long as possible.

203
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,458
Not often they get real beds.

204
00:09:12,416 --> 00:09:13,875
-[VIDAUX] Derrida...
-Hmm?

205
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,708
Before, you talked
about turning back time

206
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:18,958
in order to do the past over.

207
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:21,375
It’s alright if you
don’t believe me.

208
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:23,458
I just wanna know,
if the past got changed,

209
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:25,250
where would we be right now?

210
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:27,333
For instance,
if the two of us hadn’t met,

211
00:09:27,416 --> 00:09:30,208
and I didn’t pull you
out of that battlefield...

212
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:32,541
Assuming I got lucky
and survived, then...

213
00:09:32,625 --> 00:09:35,375
I guess I’d probably
be here, but alone.

214
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:39,250
And, the memory
of you saving me,

215
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:42,291
would be sequestered off to
an inaccessible part of my mind.

216
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,916
Like a dream you
forget upon waking.

217
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,000
[VIDAUX]
A dream...

218
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,625
But I’ve learned that I can’t

219
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:49,791
change the past
that significantly.

220
00:09:49,875 --> 00:09:51,416
The moment that I try,

221
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,500
I’m kicked back to the present.

222
00:09:53,583 --> 00:09:54,916
The most I can do

223
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,750
is say a few words
to someone, that’s all.

224
00:09:58,791 --> 00:10:00,500
I see.

225
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,208
Why’d you wanna know?

226
00:10:03,291 --> 00:10:04,708
[VIDAUX]
I’m gonna go check on Graham.

227
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:06,916
We’re moving out,
wake them up for me.

228
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:10,750
[door opens, closes]

229
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:13,208
-[breeze blowing]
-[engine humming]

230
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:15,750
[YURI]
It’s quiet.

231
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:17,041
[DERRIDA]
So far, everything’s gone

232
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:18,541
according to Cassiel’s plan.

233
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:20,625
I wouldn’t be so sure.

234
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:24,625
-[DERRIDA] Donna!
-[gun clicking]

235
00:10:24,708 --> 00:10:26,291
♪

236
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,833
[VIDAUX]
She outmaneuvered us.

237
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,416
She wants to try
and chase us down

238
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,625
in order to lure Cassiel out.

239
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:34,000
But even so, no one could
possibly hit us at this dista--

240
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:35,333
-[blast]
-[smash]

241
00:10:35,416 --> 00:10:36,291
[BOTH gasp]

242
00:10:37,916 --> 00:10:39,500
[GRAHAM] Damage to
shock-absorption system.

243
00:10:39,583 --> 00:10:40,750
Immediate stop requested.

244
00:10:40,833 --> 00:10:42,333
Yeah, like hell we’re stopping!

245
00:10:42,416 --> 00:10:44,000
[engine roar]

246
00:10:44,083 --> 00:10:45,041
[chuckle]

247
00:10:48,041 --> 00:10:49,708
We’ve gotta move!
She’s gaining on us!

248
00:10:49,791 --> 00:10:51,208
-[blast]
-[MAYUKA] Ah!

249
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:52,333
Get down!

250
00:10:54,583 --> 00:10:57,041
[tires screech]

251
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:58,250
[VIDAUX growls]

252
00:10:58,333 --> 00:11:00,333
Get outta my way,
stupid hunk of junk!

253
00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:02,250
[CASSIEL] Is that any way
to talk to your savior?

254
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,166
Cassiel!

255
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:04,666
[ramp whirring, thud]

256
00:11:09,708 --> 00:11:11,000
[engine roaring]

257
00:11:12,083 --> 00:11:13,541
[DONNA laughing]

258
00:11:13,625 --> 00:11:15,583
Well, it would seem that
I’ve finally smoked

259
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:17,000
the rat out from its hole!

260
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:18,458
Get away from her, Cassiel!

261
00:11:18,541 --> 00:11:20,125
[DONNA]
Dawn.

262
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:23,333
That’s the moment Death’s
scythe will find your neck.

263
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:24,666
Incorrect.

264
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,291
Your artificial arm
is a prototype,

265
00:11:26,375 --> 00:11:28,125
a late-generation refurbish.

266
00:11:28,208 --> 00:11:30,833
I know because I’m one of
the people who developed it.

267
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:31,750
[blast]

268
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:32,958
[grunt]

269
00:11:33,916 --> 00:11:35,833
[scream]

270
00:11:35,916 --> 00:11:37,125
[grunting]

271
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:38,666
[clattering]

272
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:43,000
[CASSIEL]
This is an anti-pulse generator.

273
00:11:43,083 --> 00:11:45,625
It simulates a command from the
brain stem to the prosthetic,

274
00:11:45,708 --> 00:11:47,291
locking it up involuntarily.

275
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,750
That’s impressive.

276
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:51,208
Did you design it?

277
00:11:51,291 --> 00:11:52,708
Very ironic.

278
00:11:52,791 --> 00:11:55,000
This device is evidence
of my original sin,

279
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:56,583
and yet it ended up
saving your life

280
00:11:56,666 --> 00:11:59,166
-10 years after its creation.
-Huh?

281
00:11:59,250 --> 00:12:00,958
Derrida Yvain.

282
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:03,083
I can’t begin to tell
you how happy I am

283
00:12:03,166 --> 00:12:05,625
that you’re still among us.
But now,

284
00:12:05,708 --> 00:12:07,416
I must apologize.

285
00:12:09,166 --> 00:12:11,083
-[energy humming]
-[VIDAUX] I see.

286
00:12:11,166 --> 00:12:13,000
So that’s why
they can’t find you.

287
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:15,208
Rebuild certainly isn’t happy

288
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,750
that I’m still pottering
around unchecked.

289
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:19,666
I couldn’t go as
far as cryostasis,

290
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:22,708
but I needed to hide
myself from them somehow.

291
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:24,708
So, I was right.
You were the one behind

292
00:12:24,791 --> 00:12:26,750
that anonymous call
I got 10 years ago.

293
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:31,333
Andrei needed an engineer’s
help for his scheme to work,

294
00:12:31,416 --> 00:12:33,125
so I altered the QC process,

295
00:12:33,208 --> 00:12:35,958
ensuring that the bug in the DZs
wouldn’t come to light in time

296
00:12:36,041 --> 00:12:37,458
for anything to
be done about it.

297
00:12:37,541 --> 00:12:41,000
I eventually decided to try
and warn you and Nathan,

298
00:12:41,083 --> 00:12:43,250
but by then it was too late.

299
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,750
I’m sorry, Cassiel.

300
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:47,000
If only I had
understood your warning.

301
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:48,166
[CASSIEL]
No.

302
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:49,625
It’s my fault for
being so vague,

303
00:12:49,708 --> 00:12:51,666
just to save my own hide.

304
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,541
If I had known then
that you’d found the bug

305
00:12:53,625 --> 00:12:54,916
and completed a patch file,

306
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,958
maybe I would've been
less of a coward.

307
00:12:57,041 --> 00:13:00,208
Because that’s something not
even Andrei could have foreseen.

308
00:13:00,291 --> 00:13:01,666
It’s impressive.

309
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:03,416
[DERRIDA] I could say
the same about that device

310
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:04,791
you used to stop Donna earlier.

311
00:13:04,875 --> 00:13:06,041
[device clinks]

312
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:07,833
Nah, this is just
something I rigged up.

313
00:13:09,041 --> 00:13:11,125
Keeping the DZ bug hidden
was such a priority

314
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:13,833
that I skipped the QA
on this unit entirely.

315
00:13:13,916 --> 00:13:17,541
And so, the defects in
the DMZ 2580 slipped right by.

316
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,708
And that’s what you meant
by your “original sin.”

317
00:13:20,791 --> 00:13:23,583
So after hiding away in
this box for so long,

318
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:25,916
why’d you decide
to help us out now?

319
00:13:26,875 --> 00:13:28,666
Atonement, perhaps.

320
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:31,583
I knew the secret,
but couldn’t make it public.

321
00:13:31,666 --> 00:13:34,541
Before long, just as I feared,
war broke out.

322
00:13:34,625 --> 00:13:36,708
I lost my wife and my children.

323
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:41,291
I was happy when Mage
showed up and asked for my help.

324
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:42,791
If there was
anything I could do,

325
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:44,791
I knew I wanted to assist her.

326
00:13:44,875 --> 00:13:47,000
What did she end
up asking of you?

327
00:13:47,083 --> 00:13:50,166
She requested various things
that would help her hold her own

328
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:52,166
and survive out
there by herself.

329
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:53,541
And one more thing,

330
00:13:53,625 --> 00:13:55,750
that I couldn’t
really understand...

331
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:57,416
She wanted furniture
and equipment

332
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:59,458
that were identical to
what she had in her home

333
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:01,625
when she was living
with her father.

334
00:14:01,708 --> 00:14:03,041
What would she
need all that for?

335
00:14:03,125 --> 00:14:06,041
She never did give me a reason.

336
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:08,875
And after that, she just said
she was going to a quiet place.

337
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,541
Wonder what that means.

338
00:14:11,625 --> 00:14:14,791
♪

339
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:17,250
Why can’t I kill him?

340
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,666
Is God protecting that man
from death at my hands?

341
00:14:26,458 --> 00:14:27,916
Angelica.

342
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,750
You poor child.

343
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:31,458
There’s no need to worry.

344
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:33,833
I have kept the damage
to a minimum.

345
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,333
You can continue to act.

346
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:38,833
Yes, and I too can
continue to act.

347
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:41,250
I cannot leave
Derrida Yvain alive.

348
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:43,458
Nor the one foolishly
trying to assist him.

349
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:45,708
Using a device like that.

350
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:48,041
Does the man think
he’s God or something?

351
00:14:48,125 --> 00:14:49,666
Oh, yes, Angelica.

352
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:52,000
He cannot be forgiven.

353
00:14:52,083 --> 00:14:53,541
[wind blowing]

354
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:56,166
This cannot be forgiven.

355
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:01,291
♪

356
00:15:03,666 --> 00:15:06,791
-Look, the water is so blue!
-[giggle] So I see!

357
00:15:06,875 --> 00:15:08,875
[footsteps]

358
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:10,333
[panting]

359
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:14,541
[heavy breathing]

360
00:15:15,875 --> 00:15:17,916
[CASSIEL]
My hideout is over this way.

361
00:15:20,041 --> 00:15:23,500
When Mage first met me, she had
just found you in cryostasis,

362
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:26,000
and was desperately
researching any possible method

363
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:27,708
she could use to unfreeze you.

364
00:15:28,666 --> 00:15:31,625
Saving you was the only
mission on her mind back then.

365
00:15:31,708 --> 00:15:33,041
Hold on a sec.

366
00:15:33,125 --> 00:15:34,208
Are you saying that the person

367
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:35,875
who got me out of
stasis was Mage?

368
00:15:35,958 --> 00:15:39,333
Does the term “Trout Theory”
ring any bells for you?

369
00:15:39,416 --> 00:15:40,625
No way.

370
00:15:41,583 --> 00:15:43,500
[CASSIEL]
Mage mentioned it many times.

371
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:47,416
She said it was an important
theory, about memory and time.

372
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,458
[wind blowing]

373
00:15:49,541 --> 00:15:51,125
-[groan]
-Derrida?

374
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:53,958
The Trout Theory was
my old research thesis

375
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:55,791
from when I was just a student.

376
00:15:55,875 --> 00:15:57,708
But experimentation
was too dangerous,

377
00:15:57,791 --> 00:15:59,541
so I never substantiated it.

378
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,458
Oh, I see.

379
00:16:01,541 --> 00:16:03,500
[DERRIDA]
It was a long time ago.

380
00:16:03,583 --> 00:16:05,666
Now that Nathan’s dead,

381
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:08,000
there’s no one left
to carry it on.

382
00:16:08,083 --> 00:16:10,083
-Except Mage.
-[DERRIDA] Huh?

383
00:16:10,166 --> 00:16:12,541
That’s why she was looking
for a quiet place.

384
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:14,958
She was going to pick up
where you and Nathan left off.

385
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:16,125
She was?

386
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,083
Then Mage is in serious danger!

387
00:16:18,166 --> 00:16:19,416
-[groaning]
-[gasp]

388
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,750
[wind howling]

389
00:16:20,833 --> 00:16:23,250
Huh? This is the time ride fog.

390
00:16:24,708 --> 00:16:26,333
[grunt, thud]

391
00:16:26,416 --> 00:16:27,791
-Derrida!
-[gasp]

392
00:16:27,875 --> 00:16:29,541
-[gasp]
-[air rushing]

393
00:16:30,708 --> 00:16:31,791
-[smash]
-[grunt]

394
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:33,875
-Run for it!
-[grunt]

395
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,083
-[slice]
-[gasp]

396
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,416
-[DERRIDA] Vidaux!
-[wind howling]

397
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:40,458
[VIDAUX groans]

398
00:16:41,416 --> 00:16:42,916
Derrida Yvain,

399
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,708
it’s time to atone for your sin.

400
00:16:44,791 --> 00:16:46,375
What’re you...

401
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:49,208
You are the son
of Jacques Yvain.

402
00:16:49,291 --> 00:16:51,416
The man who built the DZs.

403
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:52,958
The sinner who made
us what we are.

404
00:16:53,041 --> 00:16:56,166
The pretender who thinks
of himself as the Creator.

405
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:57,916
I don’t--
[groan]

406
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,625
[wind howling]

407
00:17:03,541 --> 00:17:04,791
♪

408
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:06,625
[DERRIDA]
What’s going on?

409
00:17:06,708 --> 00:17:08,916
Creator? Sinner?

410
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,208
Vidaux!

411
00:17:10,291 --> 00:17:12,250
We need to get him treatment!

412
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:14,041
[ANGE]
Time ride, irregular.

413
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:17,083
Jumping to critical point,

414
00:17:17,166 --> 00:17:20,166
-furthest from singularity.
-[clock ticking slower]

415
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:23,875
[typing]

416
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,250
Come on. Almost there.

417
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:29,208
I need to finish up this
patch file before tomorrow.

418
00:17:29,291 --> 00:17:32,416
[DERRIDA]
This is... my lab.

419
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:36,416
The day before Mage’s birthday.

420
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,166
What happened that day?

421
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:39,791
-[typing]
-[ringing]

422
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:41,666
An inter-office call?

423
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:44,000
I didn’t know anyone but me
stayed here this late.

424
00:17:44,083 --> 00:17:46,500
-[ringing continues]
-[DERRIDA] Of course!

425
00:17:46,583 --> 00:17:48,833
This must be the message
from Cassiel!

426
00:17:48,916 --> 00:17:52,500
Damn. My consciousness is weaker
than in previous time rides.

427
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:54,375
I can’t affect
anything like this!

428
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:55,750
Yes, hello?

429
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:57,500
[CASSIEL, distorted]
Derrida Yvain,

430
00:17:57,583 --> 00:18:00,333
investigate DMZ 2580.

431
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:02,708
What are you talking about?
And who is this?

432
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:05,541
[CASSIEL] The testing process
has been secretly canceled.

433
00:18:05,625 --> 00:18:07,791
If you look into it, you’ll
discover the major cover-up

434
00:18:07,875 --> 00:18:09,375
that has taken place.

435
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:11,666
[DERRIDA]
In this moment,

436
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:14,000
I already knew about the bug.

437
00:18:14,083 --> 00:18:16,041
But Cassiel didn’t know that.

438
00:18:16,125 --> 00:18:18,500
This is the office of
a senior developer.

439
00:18:18,583 --> 00:18:22,000
If you wanna request a debug,
tell a test engineer about it.

440
00:18:22,083 --> 00:18:24,083
-[CASSIEL] You’ve been advised.
-Wait.

441
00:18:25,041 --> 00:18:26,583
[DERRIDA]
Yes, good!

442
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:28,166
There has to be some way.

443
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,875
A way to change the future!

444
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:32,875
[DERRIDA]
Is this a whistleblower call?

445
00:18:33,833 --> 00:18:35,291
-[CASSIEL] Well...
-I don’t know who you are,

446
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:36,541
so you must realize...

447
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:37,875
[DERRIDA]
Should I try to convince Cassiel

448
00:18:37,958 --> 00:18:40,000
to tell me the situation?

449
00:18:40,083 --> 00:18:41,500
No...

450
00:18:41,583 --> 00:18:43,166
Considering my past self,

451
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:45,208
I’d just end up getting angry
and ruining Dad’s plan.

452
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:46,500
There must be another...

453
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,166
Do you have any
evidence of this?

454
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:49,625
[CASSIEL]
You want proof?

455
00:18:49,708 --> 00:18:51,500
I don’t have time for
a wild goose chase

456
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:53,125
stemming from
baseless information.

457
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:54,250
[groan]

458
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:55,583
[DERRIDA]
Am I reaching my limit?

459
00:18:55,666 --> 00:18:57,583
Wait! Just a little more time!

460
00:18:57,666 --> 00:19:00,000
It’s no use! [groaning]
I can’t hold on,

461
00:19:00,083 --> 00:19:01,833
and I haven’t changed
a damn thing again!

462
00:19:01,916 --> 00:19:03,000
[grunt]

463
00:19:03,083 --> 00:19:04,791
-[DONNA] What’s wrong?
-Huh?

464
00:19:04,875 --> 00:19:06,750
Derrida Yvain.

465
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:10,208
Is fear going to stop your heart
before I can have the pleasure?

466
00:19:10,291 --> 00:19:12,666
I won’t let you be a martyr.

467
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:15,666
Your punishment will be
delivered by Death itself!

468
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:16,625
[DERRIDA gasps]

469
00:19:18,041 --> 00:19:19,791
-[gasps]
-[DERRIDA grunts]

470
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:21,958
-[gasp]
-[blast]

471
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:23,458
-[sizzling]
-[groaning] Impossible!

472
00:19:23,541 --> 00:19:24,500
-[clatter]
-[gasp]

473
00:19:24,583 --> 00:19:26,125
[panting]

474
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,666
♪

475
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,000
[groaning]

476
00:19:30,958 --> 00:19:32,625
[CASSIEL]
Jump!

477
00:19:32,708 --> 00:19:34,000
[air rushing]

478
00:19:34,083 --> 00:19:35,583
[clock ticking slower]

479
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:39,458
[CASSIEL] Invert the pulse
of control test unit 25,

480
00:19:39,541 --> 00:19:42,375
and use it on DMZ 2580.

481
00:19:43,458 --> 00:19:45,000
We have those units here,

482
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:46,625
so I suppose it wouldn’t hurt.
I’ll check it later.

483
00:19:48,083 --> 00:19:50,541
I need to complete
my current project first.

484
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,708
[air rushing]

485
00:19:54,791 --> 00:19:56,333
[splash]

486
00:19:57,291 --> 00:19:59,750
[panting]

487
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:02,958
The control test unit.

488
00:20:03,041 --> 00:20:04,333
But why?

489
00:20:04,416 --> 00:20:06,500
Let’s just say I owe
it all to your advice.

490
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:07,916
Huh?

491
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,708
It’s hard to explain,
but I’ll do my best.

492
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:13,333
[sigh] If this is gonna be
a long talk, can we save it?

493
00:20:13,416 --> 00:20:15,375
[engine humming]

494
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:17,291
[DERRIDA]
Thank you again, Cassiel.

495
00:20:17,375 --> 00:20:18,791
[CASSIEL]
I meant to save you,

496
00:20:18,875 --> 00:20:20,666
but you saved me instead.

497
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:23,416
If that’s how you feel,
could I ask you a favor?

498
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,458
It’s a dangerous request,
though.

499
00:20:25,541 --> 00:20:28,125
If you want me to draw away
Donna and the bounty hunters,

500
00:20:28,208 --> 00:20:29,916
then I’ll gladly
take it on for you.

501
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,666
I won’t need too long.

502
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:33,250
Just three days.

503
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:35,791
[CASSIEL] That wound will take
at least a month to heal.

504
00:20:35,875 --> 00:20:37,708
[VIDAUX]
It’ll heal while I fight.

505
00:20:37,791 --> 00:20:41,041
We don’t have much time
before the scorched Earth blast.

506
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:42,625
[CASSIEL sighs]

507
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:44,541
I’ve spread word you’re
in a trailer heading east.

508
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:46,541
That false lead should
throw them off the scent,

509
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:47,916
at least for the time being.

510
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,125
I’ll try to hold
out for two weeks.

511
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:51,875
You do that, and we’re even.

512
00:20:51,958 --> 00:20:53,791
[DERRIDA]
Wait a minute.

513
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:55,791
Since when were
there bounty hunters?

514
00:20:55,875 --> 00:20:58,750
And what exactly is
the scorched Earth blast?

515
00:20:58,833 --> 00:20:59,625
[gasp]

516
00:20:59,708 --> 00:21:01,166
[blasts]

517
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:03,291
♪

518
00:21:03,375 --> 00:21:05,041
But those are missiles.

519
00:21:05,125 --> 00:21:07,291
[VIDAUX]
More bombing tests.

520
00:21:07,375 --> 00:21:08,625
You serious?

521
00:21:08,708 --> 00:21:10,750
They might fire off
the big one any day now,

522
00:21:10,833 --> 00:21:13,208
and then we’ll all be really--
[groan]

523
00:21:13,291 --> 00:21:15,666
-[MAYUKA whines]
-Don’t force yourself to talk!

524
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:18,708
-You’ll reopen your wound.
-Papa! No, Papa!

525
00:21:18,791 --> 00:21:20,916
Hey, no need to worry
about your old man.

526
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:28,416
Did that time ride really
cause such a massive change?

527
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,791
I had no idea it
could be so powerful.

528
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:33,875
There’s no other choice now,

529
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:36,291
I need to redo that
moment one more time!

530
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:38,708
-[clock ticking slower]
-[wind howling]

531
00:21:38,791 --> 00:21:40,375
[ANGE]
That is impossible.

532
00:21:40,458 --> 00:21:43,000
The time ride is
not all-powerful.

533
00:21:43,083 --> 00:21:47,208
Changes to any given past
event can only be made once.

534
00:21:47,291 --> 00:21:48,833
What do you mean?

535
00:21:48,916 --> 00:21:50,541
[ANGE]
Two conflicting memories

536
00:21:50,625 --> 00:21:53,208
exist together within
your consciousness.

537
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:55,500
You cannot travel
to that time again.

538
00:21:55,583 --> 00:21:57,208
You’re kidding me!

539
00:21:58,375 --> 00:22:00,500
[ANGE] Traveling back
to a certain moment,

540
00:22:00,583 --> 00:22:02,666
and the alteration
of that moment,

541
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:04,833
is allowed only once.

542
00:22:06,625 --> 00:22:08,000
[DERRIDA]
How many times

543
00:22:08,083 --> 00:22:10,708
have I time ridden without
knowing that key detail?

544
00:22:10,791 --> 00:22:12,541
How many moments

545
00:22:12,625 --> 00:22:15,166
have I rendered
permanently unchangeable?

